HB 55 Re-Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Villio
Abstract: Provides for the disclosure of identifying information of jurors.
Proposed law prohibits from inclusion in public records certain information that would
identify someone who served on a jury.
Proposed law does not apply to juror information submitted to a local government.
Proposed law creates an exception for when a court finds good cause following a motion
to disclose the identifying information.
